f%2015%20examples%20that%20BI%20found%20Oxman%20plagiarizing%20from%20a%20Wikipedia%20article%20in%20her%20dissertation.%20The%20articles%20she%20pulled%20from%20were%20primarily%20technical%2C%20covering%20topics%20like%20%26quot%3BFunctionally%20graded%20material%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3BManifolds%2C%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BConstitutive%20equation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6598939b6979d73718210a3c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223308%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20Oxman%20never%20acknowledged%20having%20pulled%20from%20Wikipedia.%20She%20didn't%20just%20lift%20text%2C%20either%3A%20She%20also%20took%20an%20illustration%20from%20the%20article%20for%20%26quot%3BHeat%20flux%26quot%3B%20without%20citing%20a%20source%2C%20despite%20requirements%20in%20the%20image's%20Creative%20Commons%20license%20to%20credit%20where%20the%20picture%20came%20from.%20It's%20not%20surprising%20that%20Oxman%20wouldn't%20credit%20Wikipedia%20in%20her%20doctoral%20dissertation%3A%20While%20Wikipedia%20is%20generally%20accurate%2C%20anyone%20can%20edit%20it%2C%20so%20teachers%20regularly%20tell%20their%20students%20that%20they%20should%20not%20cite%20the%20website%20as%20an%20authority.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22comp%20of%20raster%20graphics%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6598932c6979d73718210a2d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221551%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20a%20shame%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rick%20Norwood%2C%20a%20math%20professor%20at%20Eastern%20Tennessee%20State%20University%20who%20contributed%20a%20revision%20to%20the%20Wikipedia%20article%20on%20manifolds%20that%20Oxman%20repeated%20in%20her%20dissertation.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20imagine%20why%20anyone%20would%20do%20that%2C%20because%20anyone%20who%20knows%20even%20the%20rudiments%20of%20algebraic%20topology%20could%20come%20up%20with%20their%20own%20sentence.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cspan%3ELifting%20copy%20from%20websites%2C%20a%20textbook%2C%20and%20academic%20papers%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOxman%20works%20at%20the%20intersection%20of%20design%20and%20the%20natural%20sciences%20and%20has%20used%20the%20label%20%26quot%3Bmaterial%20ecology%26quot%3B%20to%20describe%20her%20field.%20She%20once%20talked%20on%20a%20podcast%20about%20growing%20iPhones%20from%20nature.%20Her%20team%20at%20the%20MIT%20Media%20Lab%20coaxed%20silkworms%20to%20build%20sculptures.%20She%20also%20made%20undulating%20structures%20out%20of%20natural%20materials%20like%20cellulose%20and%20chitin%2C%20the%20material%20found%20in%20shrimp%20cells.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20like%20other%20academics%2C%20she%20also%20published%20lengthy%2C%20detailed%20research%20papers%2C%20sometimes%20with%20other%20authors%20and%20sometimes%20by%20herself.%20The%20bulk%20of%20the%20plagiarism%20BI%20found%20was%20in%20her%20dissertation%2C%20which%20runs%20more%20than%20300%20pages.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWikipedia%20wasn't%20the%20only%20resource%20she%20cited%20without%20attribution%20in%20the%20paper%20that%20earned%20her%20a%20doctorate.%20In%20a%20footnote%2C%20she%20used%2054%20consecutive%20words%20without%20attribution%20from%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20040812082249%2Fhttp%3A%2F%2Fwww.rhino3d.com%2Fnurbs.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Ewebsite%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20the%20design-software%20maker%20Rhino%20to%20explain%20what%20a%20%26quot%3BNon-Uniform%20Rational%20B-Spline%26quot%3B%20is.%20She%20also%20used%20technical%20language%20about%20tessellations%20that%20matched%20language%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fweb.archive.org%2Fweb%2F20090207205605%2Fhttps%3A%2F%2Fmathworld.wolfram.com%2FTessellation.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E%3Cspan%3Efrom%20the%20website%20Wolfram%20MathWorld%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%2C%20again%2C%20she%20didn't%20cite.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShe%20plagiarized%20both%20before%20and%20after%20she%20received%20her%20Ph.D.%20in%202010.%20Of%20three%20peer-reviewed%20papers%20reviewed%20by%20BI%2C%20two%20%E2%80%94%202007's%20%26quot%3BGet%20Real%3A%20Towards%20Performance%20Driven%20Computational%20Geometry%26quot%3B%20and%202011's%20%26quot%3BVariable%20Property%20Rapid%20Prototyping%26quot%3B%20%E2%80%94%20also%20contained%20plagiarism.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202011%20paper%20included%20more%20than%20100%20words%20exactly%20as%20they%20appeared%20in%20the%202005%20book%20%26quot%3BRapid%20Manufacturing%3A%20An%20Industrial%20Revolution%20for%20the%20Digital%20Age%2C%26quot%3B%20without%20quotation%20marks%2C%20citation%2C%20or%20a%20mention%20in%20Oxman's%20bibliography.%20She%20pulled%20material%20from%20%26quot%3BPath%20planning%20of%20functionally%20graded%20material%20objects%20for%20layered%20manufacturing%2C%26quot%3B%20a%202004%20paper%20by%20M.Y.%20Zhou%2C%20without%20mentioning%20it%20in%20her%20bibliography.%20And%20she%20included%20two%20verbatim%20sentences%20from%20the%201999%20book%20%26quot%3BFunctionally%20Graded%20Materials%3A%20Design%2C%20Processing%20and%20Applications%26quot%3B%20without%20quotation%20marks%20or%20an%20in-line%20citation%2C%20though%20the%20work%20is%20mentioned%20in%20her%20bibliography.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%202007%20%26quot%3BGet%20Real%26quot%3B%20paper%20pulled%20language%20describing%20tensors%20%E2%80%94%20an%20algebraic%20concept%20that%20includes%20scalars%20and%20vectors%20%E2%80%94%20from%20an%20earlier-published%20work%2C%20the%20%26quot%3BCRC%20Concise%20Encyclopedia%20of%20Mathematics.%26quot%3B%20In%20a%202010%20paper%2C%20%26quot%3BPer%20Formative%3A%20Towards%20a%20Post%20Materialist%20Paradigm%20in%20Architecture%2C%26quot%3B%20that%20was%20not%20peer-reviewed%2C%20BI%20also%20found%20another%20instance%20of%20plagiarism%2C%20with%20Oxman%20using%20chunks%20of%20language%20from%20publisher%20Da%20Capo%20Press'%20description%20of%20%26quot%3BThe%20Modern%20Language%20of%20Architecture%26quot%3B%20by%20Bruno%20Zevi.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMIT%20did%20not%20reply%20to%20a%20request%20for%20comment%20sent%20outside%20normal%20business%20hours.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBI%20sought%20comment%20from%20Ackman%20and%20Oxman%3B%20they%20declined%20via%20a%20spokesperson.%20But%20after%20BI%20had%20emailed%20its%20findings%20to%20Oxman%2C%20Ackman%20posted%20a%20response%20on%20X%20in%20which%20he%20promised%20to%20conduct%20plagiarism%20reviews%20of%20MIT's%20leadership.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unfortunate%20that%20my%20actions%20to%20address%20problems%20in%20higher%20education%20have%20led%20to%20these%20attacks%20on%20my%20family.%20This%20experience%20has%20inspired%20me%20to%20save%20all%20news%20organizations%20from%20the%20trouble%20of%20doing%20plagiarism%20reviews%2C%26quot%3B%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FBillAckman%2Fstatus%2F1743407502312505795%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehe%20wrote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20to%20his%201%20million%20followers.%20He%20pledged%20to%20conduct%20a%20thorough%20review%20of%20MIT%20president%20Sally%20Kornbluth%2C%20all%20MIT%20faculty%2C%20and%20board%20members%20and%20other%20officers%20of%20the%20MIT%20Corporation%20for%20evidence%20of%20plagiarism%2C%20using%20MIT's%20plagiarism%20standards.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20shar