ot%3B%20including%20children%2C%20Aldrich%20said.%20The%20government%20constantly%20communicates%20their%20importance%2C%26quot%3B%20Aldrich%20said%2C%20adding%2C%20%26quot%3BAre%20you%20ready%3F%20What%20have%20you%20done%3F%20Do%20you%20know%20your%20neighbors%3F%20Can%20you%20help%20in%20a%20disaster%3F%20What%20skills%20can%20you%20bring%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222181%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Visitors%20crouch%20under%20a%20pink%20structure%20as%20an%20earthquake%20hit%20the%20region%20at%20Universal%20Studios%20Japan%20in%20Osaka%20in%202024%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65984477ec62ab5daf8122bf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EVisitors%20brace%20for%20the%202024%20earthquake%20at%20Universal%20Studios%20Japan.%3Cp%3EKyodo%20via%20REUTERS%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EStudents%20participate%20in%20earthquake%20drills%2C%20and%20the%20government%20conducts%20simulations%20to%20test%20its%20readiness.%20The%20government%20also%20recommends%20people%20keep%20an%20emergency%20kit%20ready%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20crucial%20to%20survival%20because%20affected%20regions%20can%20be%20cut%20off%20from%20emergency%20services%20for%20days%20after%20a%20disaster%2C%20just%20as%20much%20of%20the%20Noto%20Peninsula%20is%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20those%20cases%2C%20Aldrich%20said%2C%20your%20neighbors%20are%20your%20first%20responders.%20In%20over%20a%20decade%20of%20researching%20disasters%2C%20he's%20found%20that%20social%20relationships%20are%20a%20major%20predictor%20of%20survival.%20He%20said%20that%20community%20earthquake%20drills%20teach%20people%20what%20to%20do%20and%20help%20them%20trust%20their%20neighbors.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202007%2C%20the%20Japan%20Meteorological%20Society%20launched%20its%20%26quot%3BEarthquake%20Early%20Warning%20System%26quot%3B%20(EEWS).%20The%20J-Alert%20system%20can%20also%20broadcast%20to%20TVs%2C%20radios%2C%20and%20cellphones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETokyo%20even%20has%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fjun%2F02%2Fjapan-vending-machines-to-automatically-offer-free-food-if-earthquake-hits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eradio-equipped%20vending%20machine%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20sounds%20an%20alarm%20to%20park-goers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Workers%20stand%20on%20a%20road%20where%20a%20car%20is%20stuck%20on%20a%20broken%20road%20after%20an%20earthquake%20in%20Japan%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659723c16979d73718209225%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20earthquakes%20killed%20dozens%2C%20left%20thousands%20without%20power%2C%20and%20destroyed%20roads%20and%20buildings.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FKim%20Kyung-Hoon%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWarnings%20come%20through%20a%20few%20seconds%20to%20a%20few%20minutes%20before%20the%20quake%20hits%2C%20giving%20people%20some%20time%20to%20get%20to%20a%20safer%20location.%20They're%20also%20crucial%20for%20rail%20travel.%20Japan%20Railways%20trains%20automatically%20halt%20when%20the%20earthquake%20detection%20system%20kicks%20in.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202022%2C%20a%20bullet%20train%20derailed%20after%20a%207.4-magnitude%20quake%2C%20but%20none%20of%20the%2078%20passengers%20and%20crew%20were%20seriously%20injured%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fenglish.kyodonews.net%2Fnews%2F2022%2F03%2Ff2bf62a8bb81-quake-hit-bullet-train-services-to-fully-resume-around-april-20.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EKyodo%20News%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%20The%20train%20slowed%20significantly%20from%20its%20typical%20speed%20of%20up%20to%20186%20miles%20per%20hour%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.japantimes.co.jp%2Fnews%2F2022%2F03%2F18%2Fnational%2Ftohoku-train-derailment-shinkansen%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EThe%20Japan%20Times%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EJapan%20installs%20resilient%20infrastructure%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMuch%20like%20its%20buildings%2C%20Japan%20has%20the%20experience%20and%20the%20money%20to%20fortify%20its%20infrastructure%20against%20earthquakes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapanese-economic-disaster-impact-2011-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E2011%20disaster%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20rapid%20response%20teams%20were%20able%20to%20quickly%20repair%20roads%20to%20help%20move%20supplies%20and%20assistance%20to%20affected%20areas.%20In%20one%20case%2C%20a%20torn-apart%20road%20took%20only%20six%20days%20to%20fix%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2011%2Fmar%2F24%2Fjapan-disaster-reconstruction-road-recovery%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221715%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Japan%20earthquake%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F5c1edc9ddde86754cb659c4e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221286%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELocal%20residents%20look%20at%20cracks%20caused%20by%20an%20earthquake%20on%20a%20road%20in%20Mashiki%20town%2C%20Kumamoto%20prefecture%2C%20southern%20Japan%2C%20in%20this%20photo%20taken%20by%20Kyodo%20April%2016%2C%202016.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FKyodo%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%202021%20World%20Bank%20report%20said%20the%20country%20learned%20several%20lessons%20from%20the%202011%20disasters%2C%20from%20improving%20water%20supply%20infrastructure%20to%20fortifying%20backups%20to%20the%20undersea%20cables%20that%20power%20the%20internet.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAldrich%20said%20the%20biggest%20lesson%20was%20in%20revamping%20nuclear%20plant%20safety%20regulations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%202011%20Fukushima%20meltdown%2C%20Japan%20was%20slow%20to%20restart%20using%20nuclear%20power.%20The%20Japan%20Times%20reported%20that%2010%20of%20its%2033%20reactors%20are%20in%20operation%20after%20being%20shut%20down%20over%20a%20decade%20ago.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EExperts%20are%20also%20concerned%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20a%20very%20large%20%26quot%3Bmegaquake%26quot%3B%20occurring%20sometime%20in%20the%20next%20four%20decades%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theguardian.com%2Fworld%2F2023%2Fjun%2F02%2Fjapan-vending-machines-to-automatically-offer-free-food-if-earthquake-hits%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EThe%20Guardian%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202020%20a%20Japanese%20government%20panel%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesun.ie%2Fnews%2F5352026%2Fjapan-predicts-mega-earthquake-100ft-tsunami-obliterate-fukushima-plant%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewarned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20another%20large%20tsunami%20could%20inundate%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjapan-release-fukushima-nuclear-disaster-radioactive-wastewater-treated-safe-2023-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EFukushima%20Daiichi%20Nuclear%20Power%20Plant%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20any%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EThe%20double%20disaster%20of%20a%20tsunami%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222351%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20massive%20tsunami%20wave%20rushing%20over%20trees%20and%20houses%20in%20Natori%2C%20Miyagi%20Prefecture%20in%20northeastern%20Japan%20in%202011%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F659846531c5c7b8c9a0e6dc0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20massive%20tsunami%20wave%20swept%20over%20trees%20and%20houses%20in%20Natori%2C%20Japan%20in%202011.%3Cp%3EREUTERS%2FKYODO%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20reasons%20an%20earthquake%20in%20Japan%20can%20be%20so%20dangerous%20is%20the%20possibility%20of%20tsunamis.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20the%201980s%20and%20'90s%2C%20Japan%20constructed%20seawalls%20to%20hold%20back%20gigantic%20waves.%20But%20in%202011%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2011%2F07%2F05%2F137611026%2Fwhat-went-wrong-in-fukushima-the-human-factor%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E40-foot%20tsunami%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20rushed%20over%20the%2019-foot%20seawall%20at%20the%20Fukushima%20plant.%20The%20plant%20suffered%20a%20meltdown%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20a%20long%20history%20of%20disasters%2C%20the%20country%20wasn't%20fully%20prepared%20for%20the%20tsunami%20that%20developed%20following%20the%202011%20earthquake%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencedirect.com%2Fscience%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fpii%2FS2212420912000027%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3E2012%20report%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20areas%2C%20buoys%20outfitted%20with%20sensors%20monitor%20for%20tsunamis.%20As%20with%20earthquake%20alerts%2C%20the%20Japan%20Meteorological%20Agency%20uses%20TV%2C%20radio%2C%20and%20mobile%20phones%20to%20distribute%20the%20warnings.%20Sirens%20also%20sound%2C%20often%20giving%20people%20several%20minutes%20of%20warning%20that%20a%20wave%20may%20strike.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%2C%20the%202004%20Indian%20Ocean%20tsunami%20hit%20a%20number%20of%20islands%20with%20no%20formal%20warning%20system%20and%20resulted%20in%20over%20200%2C000%20deaths%2C%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.noaa.gov%2Fjetstream%2F2004tsu_max%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENOAA%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20historical%20knowledge%20may%20have%20helped%20save%20lives%20during%20Japan's%202011%20tsunami.%20Some%20survivors%20knew%20how%20far%20waters%20could%20encroach%20due%20to%20stone%20markers%20residents%20had%20placed%20after%20earlier%20tsunamis.%20Some%20of%20the%20monuments%20are%20hundreds%20of%20years%20old.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.c