ng%20an%2080-floor%20building%20and%20performing%2050%20pull-ups.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Frohit-shetty-recalls-the-time-when-akshay-kumar-performed-a-dangerous-stunt-on-his-own-reveals-the-khiladi-stars-fitness-secret%2Farticleshow%2F106579862.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22%26quot%3BFor%20Them%20To%20Decide%26quot%3B%3A%20India%20On%20Maldives%20President's%20China%20Visit%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20president%20of%20the%20Maldives%2C%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%2C%20will%20pay%20a%20state%20visit%20to%20China%20from%20Jan.%208%20to%2012%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20said%20in%20statement%20on%20Friday%2C%20in%20what%20would%20be%20a%20high-profile%20snub%20to%20the%20island%20nation's%20huge%20neighbour%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMultiple%20calls%20by%20Reuters%20to%20the%20Foreign%20Ministry%20and%20President's%20Office%20in%20Male%20on%20Friday%20-%20the%20weekend%20in%20the%20Maldives%20-%20to%20confirm%20the%20president's%20trip%20went%20unanswered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuizzu%2C%20who%20in%20November%20took%20over%20as%20president%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%20nation%20made%20up%20of%20more%20than%20a%20hundred%20islands%20dotted%20with%20luxury%20resorts%2C%20issued%20an%20election%20pledge%20to%20remove%20a%20small%20contingent%20of%20some%2075%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20in%20the%20country%20and%20alter%20the%20Maldives's%20%26quot%3BIndia%20first%26quot%3B%20policy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAsked%20to%20comment%20on%20Thursday%20about%20talk%20of%20President%20Muizzu%20making%20a%20state%20visit%20to%20China%2C%20New%20Delhi%20said%20the%20matter%20was%20out%20of%20its%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20for%20them%20to%20decide%20where%20they%20go%20and%20how%20they%20go%20about%20their%20international%20relations%2C%26quot%3B%20Indian%20Foreign%20Ministry%20Spokesperson%20Randhir%20Jaiswal%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20he%20had%20no%20update%20on%20the%20removal%20of%20Indian%20military%20personnel%20from%20the%20islands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20both%20New%20Delhi%20and%20Beijing%20are%20vying%20for%20influence%20in%20the%20region%2C%20Muizzu's%20government%20is%20considered%20to%20be%20leaning%20towards%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Maldives%20owes%20China%20about%20%241.3%20billion%2C%20according%20to%20the%20latest%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%20data.%20China%20is%20the%20Maldives'%20largest%20external%20creditor%2C%20accounting%20for%20about%2020%25%20of%20its%20total%20public%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPresident%20Muizzu%20seems%20disinclined%20to%20continue%20engaging%20India.%20His%20actions%20seem%20directed%20at%20creating%20distance%20between%20Male%20and%20Delhi.%20He%20also%20seems%20keen%20on%20a%20close%20friendship%20with%20China%2C%20which%20should%20be%20concerning%20to%20India%2C%26quot%3B%20Abhijit%20Singh%2C%20head%20of%20the%20Maritime%20Policy%20Initiative%20at%20the%20Observer%20Research%20Foundation%20think%20tank%20in%20New%20Delhi%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20President's%20trip%20to%20Beijing%2C%20before%20a%20visit%20to%20New%20Delhi%2C%20is%20a%20signal%20-%20as%20clear%20as%20any%20-%20that%20India%20is%20low%20on%20priority%20for%20this%20regime.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnlike%20most%20of%20his%20predecessors%20who%20have%20visited%20India%20first%20after%20being%20elected%2C%20Muizzu%20chose%20Turkey%20as%20his%20first%20international%20port%20of%20call.%20He%20later%20met%20Indian%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20in%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%20on%20the%20sidelines%20of%20COP28.%20The%20two%20countries%20have%20set-up%20a%20core%20group%20to%20discuss%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20Indian%20troops.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EU.S.%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20J.%20Blinken%20spoke%20with%20Foreign%20Minister%20Zameer%20on%20Thursday%2C%20the%20State%20Department%20said%20in%20a%20statement.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20Secretary%20reaffirmed%20the%20United%20States'%20commitment%20to%20strengthening%20cooperation%20with%20Maldives%2C%20a%20key%20partner%20in%20a%20free%2C%20open%2C%20secure%2C%20and%20prosperous%20Indo-Pacific%20region%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704463560000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-09%2F6q8r8r7_mohamed-muizzu-afp-_625x300_28_September_23.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffor-them-to-decide-where-they-go-india-on-maldives-presidents-china-visit-4806444%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20president%20of%20the%20Maldives%2C%20Mohamed%20Muizzu%2C%20will%20pay%20a%20state%20visit%20to%20China%20from%20Jan.%208%20to%2012%2C%20the%20Chinese%20foreign%20ministry%20said%20in%20statement%20on%20Friday%2C%20in%20what%20would%20be%20a%20high-profile%20snub%20to%20the%20island%20nation's%20huge%20neighbour%20India.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffor-them-to-decide-where-they-go-india-on-maldives-presidents-china-visit-4806444%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffor-them-to-decide-where-they-go-india-on-maldives-presidents-china-visit-4806444%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ffor-them-to-decide-where-they-go-india-on-maldives-presidents-china-visit-4806444%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Opinion%3A%20Ahead%20Of%20Elections%2C%20Treading%20With%20Caution%20On%20CAA%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EThe%20rules%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%202019%20(CAA)%20will%20be%20notified%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20scheduled%20in%20April-May%2C%20a%20senior%20Home%20Ministry%20official%20said%20recently.%20The%20official%20also%20said%20once%20the%20CAA%20rules%20are%20issued%2C%20the%20law%20can%20be%20implemented%20and%20those%20eligible%20can%20be%20granted%20Indian%20citizenship.%20The%20CAA%20amends%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%201955%20to%20facilitate%20Indian%20citizenship%20for%20non-Muslim%20migrants%20from%20Afghanistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Pakistan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Act%20makes%20religion%20a%20factor%20and%20seeks%20to%20fast-track%20citizenship%20to%20migrants%20-%20Hindus%2C%20Sikhs%2C%20Jains%2C%20Buddhists%2C%20Parsis%2C%20and%20Christians%20-%20who%20came%20to%20India%20before%20December%2031%2C%202014.%20It%20was%20passed%20in%20parliament%20in%20December%202019%20and%20later%20received%20the%20President's%20sign-off.%20The%20CAA%20notably%20excludes%20Muslim%20migrants%20from%20following%20the%20same%20citizenship%20path.%20It%20also%20says%20refugees%20will%20be%20given%20Indian%20citizenship%20if%20they%20have%20lived%20in%20India%20for%20five%20years%2C%20instead%20of%20the%2011%20years%20stipulated%20earlier.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CAA's%20implementation%20has%20been%20delayed%20for%20more%20than%20four%20years.%20The%20Home%20Ministry%20has%20been%20taking%20extensions%20since%202020%20at%20regular%20intervals%20from%20the%20parliamentary%20committees%20for%20framing%20the%20rules.%20The%20rules%20for%20any%20legislation%20need%20to%20be%20framed%20within%20six%20months%20of%20presidential%20assent.%20If%20not%2C%20then%20an%20extension%20has%20to%20be%20sought.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20proposed%20law%20provoked%20massive%20protests%20in%20Delhi.%20Hundreds%20of%20men%2C%20women%2C%20and%20children%20staged%20a%20sit-in%20for%20months%20at%20Shaheen%20Bagh%2C%20which%20became%20emblematic%20of%20the%20campaign%20against%20the%20new%20citizenship%20law.%20There%20were%20agitations%20in%20Bengal%20and%20Assam%20too%20against%20the%20CAA.%20More%20than%20200%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20Act%20have%20been%20filed%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20since%20December%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESanjay%20Hegde%2C%20Senior%20Advocate%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20says%3A%20%26quot%3BThe%20government%20legislates%20first%20but%20implements%20much%20later.%20The%20amendments%20were%20made%20in%202019%2C%20but%20rules%20for%20implementation%20have%20still%20not%20been%20made.%20The%20challenge%20against%20CAA%20is%20pending%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20but%20there%20is%20no%20stay%20on%20its%20implementation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhy%20the%20protests%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeople%20in%20Assam%20protested%20against%20the%20CAA's%20implementation%2C%20as%20they%20feared%20it%20would%20cause%20a%20rush%20of%20immigrants%20into%20the%20state%20and%20result%20in%20demographic%2C%20cultural%2C%20and%20linguistic%20changes.%20The%20CAA%20doesn't%20apply%20to%20the%20tribal%20areas%20of%20other%20northeastern%20states%20(these%20are%20protected%20under%20the%20Sixth%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution)%20and%20the%20area%20covered%20under%20'The%20Inner%20line'%20notified%20under%20the%20Bengal%20Eastern%20Frontier%20Regulation%2C%201873.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20places%20like%20Delhi%20and%20Bengal%2C%20the%20protests%20were%20against%20the%20exclusion%20of%20Muslims.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20parties%20and%20other%20critics%20have%20termed%20the%20Act%20as%20discriminatory%20and%20against%20the%20basic%20ethos%20of%20the%20Constitution%20as%20it%20excludes%20Muslims%2C%20the%20largest%20minority%20community%20in%20India.%20Any%20law%20made%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20religion%20is%20unconstitutional%2C%20the%20opposition%20asserts.%20Amid%20reports%20that%20the%20CAA%20rules%20will%20be%20enforced%20just%20before%20the%20elections%2C%20the%20opposition%20is%20accusing%20the%20BJP%20government%20of%20using%20the%20CAA%20to%20polarise%20voters.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20fact%20that%20the%20implementation%20is%20being%20promised%20nearer%20to%20the%20general%20election%20shows%20the%20government's%20intentions%20to%20activate%20its%20core%20constituencies%20by%20polarising%20the%20issue%20again.%20It%20would%20have%20been%20wiser%20to%20let%20the%20next%20elected%20government%20take%20a%20final%20call%20in%20a%20few%20months'%20time.%20But%20wisdom%20and%20political%20campaigns%20seldom%20go%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Sanjay%20Hegde.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Government's%20stand%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20has%20denied%20that%20the%20CAA%20is%20discriminatory.%20The%20citizenship%20law%20was%20part%20of%20the%20BJP's%20manifesto%20in%20the%202014%20and%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20It%20has%20also%20been%20a%20big%20theme%20during%20the%20party's%20campaign%20for%20the%20West%20Bengal%20election.%20The%20BJP's%20think%20tank%20feels%20CAA%20is%20among%20the%20reasons%20for%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20party%20in%20West%20Bengal.%20In%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%20scooped%2018%20of%20Bengal's%2042%20seats%20and%20a%2040.2%20per%20cent%20vote%20share%2C%20upsetting%20Mamata%20Banerjee's%20Trinamool%20Congress.%20In%20the%202021%20Bengal%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%2077%20seats%20in%20the%20294-member%20assembly%2C%20registering%20a%20remarkable%20growth%20since%202011%2C%20when%20it%20had%20failed%20to%20open%20its%20account.%20Even%20in%20December%2C%20Home%20Minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20while%20addressing%20a%20BJP%20meeting%20in%20Kolkata%2C%20reiterated%20the%20party's%20commitment%20to%20the%20CAA%2C%20much%20to%20the%20chagrin%20of%20Bengal%20Chief%20Minister%20Mamata%20Banerjee%2C%20who%20has%20opposed%20the%20Act.%20%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAshwini%20Kumar%20Upadhyay%2C%20Supreme%20Court%20advocate%20and%20the%20lone%20petitioner%20in%20support%20of%20the%20CAA%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BA%20large%20section%20of%20the%20Bengali%20Hindu%20community%20fled%20East%20Pakistan%20and%20migrated%20to%20West%20Bengal%20in%201960s%20to%20save%20themselves%20from%20religious%20persecution.%20No%20one%20bothered%20about%20them.%20Now%2C%20when%20the%20BJP%20government%20paved%20the%20way%20for%20realising%20the%20dream%20of%20citizenship%20to%20the%20Bengali%20Hindus%20and%20other%20persecuted%20communities%2C%20everyone%20including%20the%20TMC%20(Trinamool)%20is%20opposing%20it.%20Similarly%2C%20the%20people%20of%20Assam%20realise%20the%20conspiracy%20of%20changing%20their%20state's%20demography%20through%20illegal%20Muslim%20infiltration.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20look%20at%20the%20Home%20Ministry's%20annual%20report%20for%202021-22%20reveals%20that%201%2C414%20foreigners%20belonging%20to%20minority%20communities%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan%20were%20granted%20Indian%20citizenship%20by%20registration%20or%20naturalisation%20under%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%2C%201955.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20district%20magistrates%20of%2029%20districts%20and%20Home%20Secretaries%20of%20nine%20states%2C%20Gujarat%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20Haryana%2C%20Punjab%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Delhi%2C%20and%20Maharashtra%2C%20have%20been%20authorised%20to%20grant%20citizenship%20to%20foreigners%20belonging%20to%20the%20six%20communities%20from%20Pakistan%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20and%20Afghanistan.%20Interestingly%2C%20officials%20from%20Assam%20and%20Bengal%2C%20where%20CAA%20is%20a%20burning%20political%20issue%2C%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20granted%20similar%20authority.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20concern%20that%20a%20blend%20of%20CAA%20with%20the%20proposed%20All%20India%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20rob%20many%20Muslims%20staying%20in%20India%20of%20full%20citizenship.%20To%20counter%20this%20claim%2C%20Mr%20Upadhyay%20says%2C%20%26quot%3BThe%20propaganda%20that%20CAA%20compromises%20with%20the%20secular%20character%20of%20the%20Constitution%20and%20is%20anti-Muslim%20needs%20to%20be%20clarified%20to%20expose%20the%20hypocrisy%20and%20double%20standards%20of%20political%20parties.%20The%20Act%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20Indian%20Muslims%20and%20they%20need%20not%20be%20worried.%20It%20is%20not%20meant%20to%20take%20away%20anyone's%20citizenship%20but%20to%20confer%20citizenship.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20needs%20to%20address%20these%20concerns%20through%20talks%20and%20mass%20dissemination%20of%20correct%20information%20on%20the%20CAA%2C%20lest%20it%20blows%20up%20in%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%20national%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Bharti%20Mishra%20Nath%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author.%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704463500000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2020-01%2F51982p4g_caa-protest-esplanade_625x300_22_January_20.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fahead-of-elections-treading-with-caution-on-caa-4806443%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20rules%20of%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%202019%20(CAA)%20will%20be%20notified%20before%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20scheduled%20in%20April-May%2C%20a%20senior%20Home%20Ministry%20official%20said%20recently.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fahead-of-elections-treading-with-caution-on-caa-4806443%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fahead-of-elections-treading-with-caution-on-caa-4806443%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fopinion%2Fahead-of-elections-treading-with-caution-on-caa-4806443%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Israeli%20minister%20lays%20out%20post-war%20Gaza%20plan%20as%20fighting%20rages%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704463476000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-106579760%2Cimgsize-442431.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisraeli-minister-lays-out-post-war-gaza-plan-as-fighting-rages%2Farticleshow%2F106578379.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F106578379.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%20Israel's%20defence%20minister%20has%20publicly%20presented%20for%20the%20first%20time%20proposals%20for%20the%20post-war%20administration%20of%20Gaza%2C%20where%20officials%20said%20Friday%20unrelenting%20bombardment%20has%20killed%20dozens%20over%2024%20hours.%20Defence%20minister%20Yoav%20Gallant's%20plan%20for%20the%20%26quot%3Bday%20after%26quot%3B%2C%20shared%20with%20the%20media%20late%20Thursday%20but%20not%20yet%20adopted%20by%20Israel's%20war%20cabinet%2C%20says%20that%20neither%20Israel%20nor%20Hamas%20will%20govern%20Gaza%20and%20rejects%20future%20Jewish%20settlements%20there.%20The%20minister's%20broad%20outline%20was%20unveiled%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20US%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Antony%20Blinken's%20fourth%20trip%20to%20the%20region%20since%20a%20Hamas%20attack%20on%20October%207%20triggered%20the%20war.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisraeli-minister-lays-out-post-war-gaza-plan-as-fighting-rages%2Farticleshow%2F106578379.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm-timesofindia-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisraeli-minister-lays-out-post-war-gaza-plan-as-fighting-rages%2Famp_articleshow%2F106578379.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fm.timesofindia.com%2Fworld%2Fmiddle-east%2Fisraeli-minister-lays-out-post-war-gaza-plan-as-fighting-rages%2Famp_articleshow%2F106578379.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Reasons%20For%20CERT-IN's%20Exemption%20From%20RTI%20Provisions%20Are%20%E2%80%98Secret%E2%80%99%2C%20DoPT%20Says%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F12193303%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-12-at-7.32.14-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%E2%80%99s%20Department%20of%20Personnel%20and%20Training%20(DoPT)%20has%20refused%20to%20disclose%20documentary%20records%20that%20exempt%20the%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20(CERT-IN)%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20the%20Right%20to%20Information%20(RTI)%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CERT%20is%20the%20national%20nodal%20agency%20for%20responding%20to%20computer%20security%20incidents%20as%20and%20when%20they%20occur.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20information%20was%20sought%20by%20RTI%20activist%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%20following%20a%20gazette%20notification%20on%20November%2023%2C%20which%20stated%20that%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20was%20amended%20to%20include%20the%20CERT.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20implies%20that%20the%20CERT%20will%20be%20exempt%20from%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20except%20in%20cases%20where%20the%20information%20is%20sought%20in%20cases%20of%20allegations%20of%20corruption%20or%20human%20rights%20violations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20RTI%20request%2C%20Nayak%20sought%20a%20copy%20of%20the%20cabinet%20note%20relating%20to%20the%20amendment%20of%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%20the%20note%20put%20up%20for%20the%20consideration%20of%20the%20committee%20of%20secretaries%20containing%20the%20proposal%20relating%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%2C%20a%20copy%20of%20all%20documents%20relating%20to%20the%20inter-ministerial%20consultations%20held%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%20proposal%20till%20date%2C%20along%20with%20all%20file%20notings%20and%20correspondence%20held%20in%20paper%20and%20electronic%20form%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20said%20amendment%20proposal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20sought%20a%20copy%20of%20all%20official%20records%20demonstrating%20compliance%20with%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20DoPT%20committee%20headed%20by%20the%20then-joint%20secretary%2C%20Devesh%20Chaturvedi%2C%20in%202015%20regarding%20the%20procedure%20for%20notifying%20new%20organisations%20under%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20in%20relation%20to%20the%20aforementioned%20amendment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENayak%E2%80%99s%20RTI%20request%20referred%20to%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20recommendations%20in%202015%20that%20proper%20guidelines%20be%20adopted%20to%20ensure%20wide%20public%20consultation%20prior%20to%20any%20body%20being%20exempted%20from%20the%20RTI%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20committee%20also%20recommended%20that%20prior%20to%20the%20government%20issuing%20a%20notification%20under%20Section%2024(2)%20%E2%80%93%20which%20empowers%20it%20to%20amend%20the%20second%20schedule%20%E2%80%93%20the%20name%20of%20the%20proposed%20body%2C%20the%20details%20of%20its%20functioning%20and%20an%20explanation%20on%20how%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20responds%20to%20grounds%20set%20out%20under%20Section%2024%20should%20be%20publicly%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20specified%20time-frame%20should%20be%20allowed%20for%20members%20of%20the%20public%20to%20raise%20objections%20to%20the%20proposal%2C%20the%20committee%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20would%20also%20be%20in%20line%20with%20the%20proactive%20disclosures%20required%20under%20Sections%204(c)%20and%20(d)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20and%20the%20Pre-Legislative%20Consultation%20Policy%20(PCLP)%20of%20the%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20notifications%20under%20Section%2024%20by%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20must%20comprehensively%20and%20explicitly%20specify%20how%20the%20organisation%20that%20is%20being%20exempted%20fits%20into%20the%20definition%20of%20%E2%80%9Cintelligence%20and%20security%20organisations%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20reply%20on%20December%2028%2C%202023%2C%20the%20DoPT%20said%20that%20%E2%80%9CSection%2024%20of%20the%20RTI%20act%20provides%20that%20nothing%20contained%20in%20this%20Act%20shall%20apply%20to%20the%20intelligence%20and%20security%20organisations%20specified%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20proposal%20of%20exemption%20of%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20from%20the%20ambit%20of%20RTI%20Act%20has%20been%20dealt%20in%20File%20No.%201%2F3%2F2021-IR%20II%20which%20relates%20to%20amendment%20in%20second%20schedule%20to%20the%20RTI%20Act%2C%202005.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20said%20that%20the%20information%20regarding%20CERT%E2%80%99s%20inclusion%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20was%20of%20%E2%80%9Csecret%20nature.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20information%20provided%20by%20the%20organisations%20concerned%20including%20Indian%20Computer%20Emergency%20Response%20Team%20for%20their%20inclusion%20in%20the%20second%20schedule%20is%20of%20secret%20nature%20and%20exempted%20under%20Section%208(1)(a)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20i.e.%20information%2C%20disclosure%20of%20which%20would%20prejudicially%20affect%20the%20sovereignty%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%2C%20the%20security%2C%20strategic%2C%20scientific%20or%20economic%20interests%20of%20the%20state%2C%20relation%20with%20foreign%20state%20or%20lead%20to%20incitement%20of%20an%20offence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFurther%2C%20information%20is%20also%20exempted%20under%20Section%208(1)(i)%20of%20the%20RTI%20Act%20being%20record%20of%20deliberations%20of%20Secretaries%20and%20other%20officers%20and%20part%20of%20the%20Note%20for%20Committee%20of%20Secretaries%20which%20itself%20is%20Secret%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20added%20that%20the%202015%20committee%20recommendations%20were%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20accepted%20by%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CHence%2C%20compliance%20with%20the%20said%20recommendations%20does%20not%20arise.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20to%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Nayak%20said%20that%20the%20refusal%20to%20provide%20the%20documents%20is%20%E2%80%9Cintriguing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20refusal%20is%20simply%20intriguing%20because%20when%20the%20NDA%20government%20decided%20to%20include%20the%20Strategic%20Forces%20Command%20(SFC)%20under%20the%20excluded%20list%2C%20the%20CPIO%20gave%20me%20all%20the%20information%20including%20file%20noting%20and%20correspondence%20and%20the%20note%20put%20up%20to%20the%20committee%20of%20secretaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20looks%20like%20the%20Government%20is%20treating%20CERT-IN%20as%20more%20strategic%20to%20our%20security%20interests%20than%20the%20SFC%2C%20which%20looks%20after%20our%20strategic%20and%20defence%20assets%20including%20nuclear%20weapons.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704463203000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F12193303%2FScreen-Shot-2021-04-12-at-7.32.14-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Finfo-on-cert-in-inclusion-rti-exempt-orgs-is-secret%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Activist%20Venkatesh%20Nayak%20had%20sought%20to%20know%20through%20an%20RTI%20filed%20in%20November%20about%20the%20deliberations%20behind%20the%20inclusion%20of%20the%20CERT-IN%20in%20the%20list%20of%20organisations%20that%20are%20exempt%20from%20the%20RTI%20Act's%20ambit.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Finfo-on-cert-in-inclusion-rti-exempt-orgs-is-secret%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22At%20Rs%20259%20Crore%2C%20BJP%20Received%2070%25%20of%20Donations%20by%20Electoral%20Trusts%20in%202022-23%3A%20ECI%20Data%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F01145249%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20received%20over%2070%25%20of%20the%20total%20donations%20by%20electoral%20trusts%20in%202022-23%2C%20according%20to%20data%20shared%20by%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20(ECI).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20saffron%20party%20received%20Rs%20259.08%20crore%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20366%20crore%20collected%20by%20five%20electoral%20trusts%20that%20submitted%20their%20annual%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20highest%20corporate%20donation%20of%20Rs%2087%20crore%20came%20from%20Megha%20Engineering%20and%20Infrastructures.%20Serum%20Institute%20of%20India%20and%20ArcelorMittal%20Nippon%20Steel%20gave%20Rs%2050.25%20crore%20and%20Rs%2050%20crore%2C%20respectively%2C%20in%20political%20funding%20through%20these%20trusts.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20trusts%20were%20introduced%20by%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance-II%20regime%20in%202013%20to%20facilitate%20donations%20to%20political%20parties%20by%20corporations%20and%20individuals.%20However%2C%20unlike%20anonymous%20electoral%20bonds%2C%20the%20trusts%20are%20supposed%20to%20declare%20their%20donation%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI%20every%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EElectoral%20trusts%20are%20required%20by%20rules%20to%20distribute%20at%20least%2095%25%20of%20their%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%20In%202022-23%2C%20however%2C%20these%20trusts%20distributed%2099.99%25%20of%20their%20donations%20to%20political%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202022-23%2C%2013%20out%20of%20the%2018%20electoral%20trusts%2C%20registered%20with%20the%20Central%20Board%20of%20Direct%20Taxes%2C%20submitted%20their%20reports%20to%20the%20ECI.%20The%20reports%20show%20that%20only%20five%20trusts%20received%20donations%20from%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20out%20of%20a%20total%20of%20Rs%20366%20crore%20received%20by%20the%20five%20trusts%20from%2039%20corporates%2C%20over%2090%25%20contributions%20came%20from%2010%20business%20houses%2C%20an%20analysis%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR)%20shows.%20Out%20of%20the%20total%20donations%2C%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%20alone%20received%20Rs%20360.46%20crore%2C%20with%20Rs%20332.26%20crore%20coming%20from%20the%20top%2010%20corporates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221173%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688.png%201173w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688-300x141.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190137%2Fimage-1688-1024x483.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691774%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22553%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20ADR%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20comparison%2C%20only%20one%20company%20contributed%20Rs%202%20crore%20to%20Samaj%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20two%20companies%20contributed%20Rs%2075.50%20lakh%20to%20Paribartan%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20and%20two%20companies%20contributed%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20to%20Triumph%20Electoral%20Trust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2011%20individuals%20contributed%20to%20electoral%20trusts%20in%202022-23.%20%E2%80%9CEight%20individuals%20contributed%20Rs%202.70%20crore%20to%20Prudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20three%20individuals%20contributed%20Rs%208%20lakh%20to%20Einzigartig%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20ADR%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20went%20to%20the%20BJP%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrudent%20Electoral%20Trust%20donated%20the%20lion%E2%80%99s%20share%20of%20its%20contributions%20to%20the%20BJP%20(Rs%20256.25%20crore).%20It%20donated%20the%20rest%20of%20its%20donations%20to%20other%20political%20parties%2C%20such%20as%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(Rs%2090%20crore)%2C%20and%20the%20remaining%20Rs%2017%20crore%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20YSR%20Congress%2C%20and%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESamaj%20donated%20Rs%201.50%20crore%20to%20the%20saffron%20party.%20The%20Congress%20received%20only%20Rs%2050%20lakh%20from%20Samaj.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22863%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689.png%20863w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05190037%2Fimage-1689-300x153.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-691770%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22441%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20ADR%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrudent%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20earlier%20known%20as%20Satya%20Electoral%20Trust%2C%20has%20consistently%20received%20the%20maximum%20share%20of%20contributions%20among%20all%20the%20other%20registered%20electoral%20trusts.%20Among%20its%20donors%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businesstoday.in%2Flatest%2Fcorporate%2Fstory%2Fprudent-electoral-trust-richest-trust-gives-rs-144-cr-of-rs-169-cr-funds-bjp-fy18-154942-2018-11-05%5C%22%