7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Jaws%20Turns%2050%3A%20Here%E2%80%99s%20How%20the%20Novel%20Differed%20From%20Its%20Film%20Adaptation%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05174532%2FScreenshot-2024-01-05-at-5.45.03-PM.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EHow%20many%20times%20have%20you%20come%20out%20of%20the%20cinema%20and%20heard%20someone%20snidely%20remark%20they%20preferred%20the%20book%2C%20as%20though%20this%20somehow%20connects%20them%20to%20a%20richer%2C%20more%20highbrow%20tradition%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20might%20ring%20true%20when%20it%20comes%20to%20literary%20masterworks%20like%20F.%20Scott%20Fitzgerald%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Gatsby%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20adapted%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt1343092%2F%5C%22%3Eso-so%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0071577%2F%5C%22%3Eversions%3C%2Fa%3E%20nearly%20four%20decades%20apart%20(equally%20dull%2C%20for%20almost%20opposite%20reasons).%20But%20the%20reverse%20is%20often%20the%20case%20with%20popular%20fiction%2C%20which%20benefits%20from%20the%20immersive%2C%20visceral%20quality%20of%20the%20cinema.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPeter%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%201974%20novel%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.panmacmillan.com.au%2F9781447220039%2F%5C%22%3EJaws%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20turns%2050%20this%20year%2C%20was%20a%20smash.%20Despite%20critics%E2%80%99%20reservations%2C%20it%20was%20on%20the%20New%20York%20Times%20bestseller%20list%20for%2044%20weeks.%20Yet%20when%20we%20think%20of%20%3Cem%3EJaws%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20images%20from%20Steven%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%201975%20film%20adaptation%20are%20what%20come%20to%20mind%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20John%20Williams%E2%80%99%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fyoutu.be%2FE-sX2Y0W8l0%3Fsi%3D7H4TUsSRrImq_eh-%5C%22%3Eiconic%20theme%20music%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpielberg%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0073195%2F%5C%22%3EJaws%3C%2Fa%3E%20keeps%20the%20simple%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20and%20stunning%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0%20narrative%20architecture%20of%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20intact.%20A%20shark%20terrorises%20a%20small%20beach%20community%20that%20depends%20on%20wealthy%20tourists%20for%20sustenance.%20Brody%2C%20the%20chief%20of%20police%2C%20keeps%20the%20beaches%20open%20due%20to%20political%20pressure%20from%20Mayor%20Vaughan%3B%20when%20more%20attacks%20occur%2C%20marine%20biologist%20Matt%20Hooper%20comes%20to%20help.%20Together%2C%20they%20contract%20wild%20shark%20hunter%20Quint%20to%20help%20them%20kill%20the%20great%20white.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20tone%20of%20grand%20adventure%20that%20defines%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20film%20marks%20a%20major%20departure%20from%20the%20novel.%20In%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20work%2C%20more%20energy%20is%20directed%20towards%20exploring%20the%20minor%20social%20and%20political%20lives%20of%20its%20small-town%20denizens%20than%20in%20staging%20an%20epic%20showdown%20between%20man%20and%20beast%20%E2%80%93%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20it%20differs%20radically%20from%20the%20film%20in%20its%20characterisation.%20In%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20world%2C%20the%20main%20characters%20are%20likeable%2C%20heroic%2C%20whereas%20in%20the%20novel%20they%E2%80%99re%20petty%2C%20broken%20and%20bitter%2C%20wading%20through%20the%20messes%20their%20personal%20lives%20have%20become.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20differences%20are%20not%20simply%20evidence%20of%20a%20young%20director%E2%80%99s%20desire%20to%20make%20the%20material%20his%20own.%20They%20map%20the%20changing%20consciousness%20of%20American%20popular%20culture%20in%20the%201970s%2C%20from%20a%20resolute%20focus%20on%20the%20violence%20simmering%20within%20United%20States%20society%20and%20policy%20(the%20civil%20rights%20movement%20and%20the%20Vietnam%20War)%20to%20an%20attempt%20to%20forget%20about%20these%20things%20through%20spectacular%2C%20anodyne%20entertainment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20we%20know%2C%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20film%20reshaped%20Hollywood%2C%20virtually%20single-handedly%20inventing%20the%20%E2%80%9Cblockbuster%E2%80%9D%20and%20marking%20a%20significant%20shift%20away%20from%20the%20existentially%20charged%2C%20sometimes%20nihilistic%2C%20ever%20self-critical%20films%20of%20the%20previous%20decade%20or%20so.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20two%20dominant%20themes%20situating%20Benchley%E2%80%99s%20novel%20in%20a%20rich%20American%20literary%20tradition%20also%20underpin%20the%20film%3A%20its%20biting%20look%20at%20small-town%20politics%20and%20economics%2C%20and%20its%20reverent%20study%20of%20a%20wilderness%20awesome%20and%20sublime.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%E2%80%98The%20shark%20material%20is%20brilliant%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20core%20is%20a%20swift%2C%20economically%20told%20tale%20of%20human%20versus%20beast%3A%20a%20classic%20American%20adventure%20in%20the%20vein%20of%20Jack%20London%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fwhite-fang-9780241652664%5C%22%3EWhite%20Fang%3C%2Fa%3E%20or%20Herman%20Melville%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.com.au%2Fbooks%2Fmoby--dick-9780451532282%5C%22%3EMoby-Dick%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBenchley%20punctuates%20this%20drama%20with%20a%20keen%20interrogation%20of%20the%20social%20dynamics%20of%20small%20American%20communities%20in%20the%20context%20of%20the%20economic%20pressures%20of%20capitalism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20career%20journalist%2C%20Benchley%20is%20effective%20in%20describing%20actions%2C%20events%20and%20scenery%3A%20shark%20hunting%2C%20the%20ocean%2C%20Quint%E2%80%99s%20boat.%20The%20shark%20material%20is%20brilliant%20%E2%80%93%20the%20few%20times%20it%20cuts%20to%20the%20shark%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20(recalling%20Spielberg%E2%80%99s%20redeployment%20of%20the%20creature%E2%80%99s%20point%20of%20view%20from%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imdb.com%2Ftitle%2Ftt0046876%2F%5C%22%3ECreature%20from%20the%20Black%20Lagoon%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20the%20writing%20becomes%20electric%2C%20effortless.%20Benchley%20is%20at%20his%20best%20when%20describing%20the%20movements%20of%20the%20shark%20in%20the%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20when%20Hooper%20is%20cage%20diving%2C%20towards%20the%20end%20of%20the%20novel%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20head%20was%20only%20a%20few%20feet%20from%20the%20cage%20when%20the%20fish%20turned%20and%20began%20to%20pass%20before%20Hooper%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20%E2%80%93%20casually%2C%20as%20if%20in%20proud%20display%20of%20its%20incalculable%20mass%20and%20power.%20The%20snout%20passed%20first%2C%20then%20the%20jaw%2C%20slack%20and%20smiling%2C%20armed%20with%20row%20upon%20row%20of%20serrate%20triangles.%20And%20then%20the%20black%2C%20fathomless%20eye%2C%20seemingly%20riveted%20upon%20him.%20The%20gills%20rippled%20%E2%80%93%20bloodless%20wounds%20in%20the%20steely%20skin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20material%20about%20people%20is%20less%20confident%20%E2%80%93%20the%20writing%20is%20uneven%20and%20trite%20in%20places%2C%20with%20moments%20between%20characters%20sometimes%20strained%20in%20order%20to%20generate%20the%20necessary%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20includes%20two%20subplots%20Spielberg%20and%20team%20wisely%20cut%20from%20the%20film.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20first%20involves%20a%20murky%20connection%20between%20Mayor%20Vaughn%20and%20the%20Mob%20that%20is%20partly%20responsible%20for%20his%20desire%20to%20keep%20the%20beaches%20open%2C%20despite%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20warnings.%20It%20seems%20both%20underdeveloped%20%E2%80%93%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20find%20out%20much%20about%20it%20%E2%80%93%20and%20strangely%20present%2C%20with%20the%20majority%20of%20the%20novel%E2%80%99s%20scenes%20involving%20the%20mayor%20gesturing%20towards%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20second%2C%20which%20probably%20would%20have%20been%20fatal%20to%20the%20film%2C%20involves%20an%20affair%20between%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20wife%20Ellen%20and%20Matt%20Hooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECharacters%20%E2%80%98loathsome%20in%20places%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20great%20joys%20of%20the%20film%20is%20the%20developing%20friendship%20between%20Hooper%20and%20Brody%2C%20culminating%20in%20their%20delightful%20final%20exchange.%20After%20the%20shark%20is%20dead%20and%20they%20are%20kicking%20their%20way%20back%20to%20shore%2C%20Brody%20laughs%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20used%20to%20hate%20the%20water.%E2%80%9D%20Hooper%20replies%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%20imagine%20why%E2%80%9D.%20Both%20men%20are%20happy%20to%20have%20survived%2C%20and%20to%20have%20each%20other.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20novel%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20more%20or%20less%20hate%20at%20first%20sight%2C%20with%20Brody%20immediately%20resenting%20Hooper%20because%20he%20grew%20up%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csummer%20person%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20area.%20Brody%20is%20ashamed%20he%E2%80%99s%20not%20one%20of%20the%20wealthy%20summer%20people%2C%20and%20tries%20to%20hide%20this%20through%20a%20kind%20of%20pathetic%20machismo%2C%20which%20emerges%20most%20visibly%20in%20his%20competitiveness%20with%20Hooper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20obsession%20with%20summer%20people%20defines%20much%20of%20the%20dialogue%20between%20Brody%20and%20Ellen%2C%20with%20Brody%E2%80%99s%20resentment%20of%20the%20summer%20people%E2%80%99s%20nonchalant%20and%20emasculating%20wealth%20matched%20by%20Ellen%E2%80%99s%20resentment%20of%20the%20fact%20she%20used%20to%20be%20a%20summer%20person%20before%20she%20married%20this%20oaf%20of%20a%20police%20chief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F565548%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231213-23-ko2crz.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px