E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livemint.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Fthe-road-to-enter-bankruptcy-court-is-now-7-000-companies-long-11704391030798.html%5C%22%3Equoted%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20authority%20in%20the%20know%20of%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20present%2C%20there%20are%202%2C001%20cases%20which%20are%20being%20heard%20by%20various%20benches%20of%20the%20tribunal.%20Between%202016%20and%20September%202023%2C%20the%20tribunal%20closed%205%2C057%20cases.%20Of%20the%205%2C057%20cases%2C%20the%20tribunal%20approved%20resolutions%20in%2015.9%25%20of%20cases%3B%20in%2039.5%25%20of%20cases%2C%20the%20resolution%20was%20either%20settled%20or%20withdrawn%2C%20and%20liquidation%20was%20ordered%20in%20the%20case%20of%2044.4%25%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20staff%20crunch%2C%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F587-vidarbha-industries-power-ltd-v-axis-bank-ltd-12-july-2022-425711.pdf%5C%22%3ESupreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%20ruling%20of%20July%202022%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20also%20making%20it%20difficult%20for%20the%20creditors%20for%20a%20bankruptcy%20rescue%2C%20another%20source%20told%20the%20newspaper.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMost%20of%20the%20companies%20(about%20two-thirds)%20waiting%20for%20NCLT%E2%80%99s%20decision%20concerning%20the%20admission%20of%20bankruptcy%20petitions%20fall%20in%20the%20manufacturing%2C%20real%20estate%2C%20and%20trading%20businesses%20sectors%2C%20indicating%20the%20prevailing%20stress%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20earlier%20case%20concerning%20Vidarbha%20Industries%20Power%20Ltd%20and%20Axis%20Bank%20Ltd%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20ruled%20that%20the%20existence%20of%20debt%20and%20its%20default%20does%20not%20automatically%20mean%20the%20case%20has%20to%20be%20admitted%20for%20bankruptcy%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20top%20court%20had%20said%20that%20it%20was%20wrong%20on%20the%20part%20of%20NCLT%20and%20its%20appellate%20tribunal%20to%20hold%20a%20view%20that%20if%2