%2C%20and%20anti-government%20protestors.%20While%20this%20would%20mean%20a%20totalitarian%20fracturing%20of%20American%20democracy%2C%20the%20potential%20consequences%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20world%20are%20even%20more%20grave.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20intends%20to%20stop%20war%20aid%20for%20Ukraine%20and%20will%20probably%20pull%20out%20of%20NATO%2C%20giving%20Russia%20a%20free%20hand%20to%20annex%20Ukraine.%20He%20is%20also%20unlikely%20to%20oppose%20China%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20invade%20Taiwan.%20This%20would%20mean%20the%20end%20of%20the%20post-Second%20World%20War%20liberal%20order%20which%20put%20an%20end%20to%20major%20wars%20of%20territorial%20conquest%2C%20ending%20the%20endemic%20political%20instability%20that%20characterised%20world%20empires%20till%20the%2019%3Cspan%3Eth%3C%2Fspan%3E%20century.%20But%20the%20greatest%20threat%20comes%20from%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20climate%20change%20denialism%20which%20could%20cripple%20global%20efforts%20to%20save%20humanity%20from%20the%20climate%20crisis.%20Canadian%20President%20Justin%20Trudeau%20on%20Friday%20said%20that%20if%20Trump%20becomes%20president%20his%20climate%20change%20policies%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Ca%20menace%20not%20just%20to%20Canada%20but%20the%20whole%20world%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20be%20higher%2C%20especially%20since%20incumbent%20Joe%20Biden%20is%20trailing%20Trump%20in%20every%20swing%20state%20by%20as%20much%20as%202%20to%205%20percentage%20points%2C%20according%20to%20polls.%20And%20in%20what%20is%20probably%20the%20most%20consequential%20case%20to%20come%20before%20any%20court%2C%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20is%20expected%20in%20January%20to%20decide%20if%20Trump%20should%20be%20barred%20from%20running%20for%20president.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20essentially%20have%20to%20decide%20two%20things.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPolitical%2C%20legal%2C%20and%20institutional%20complexities%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirstly%2C%20whether%20Trump%20participated%20in%20the%20January%206%20insurrection%20on%20Capitol%20Hill.%20And%20if%20he%20did%20so%2C%20whether%20he%20is%20barred%20from%20holding%20public%20office%20under%20the%2014th%20Amendment%20to%20the%20US%20constitution.%20The%2014th%20Amendment%20disbars%20any%20public%20official%20involved%20in%20an%20insurrection%20against%20the%20United%20States%2C%20from%20holding%20public%20office%20for%20life.%20Last%20week%2C%20an%20appeals%20court%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Colorado%2C%20ruled%20in%20the%20affirmative%20to%20both%20these%20questions.%20This%20ruling%20effectively%20bars%20Trump%20from%20the%20ballot%20in%20Colorado.%20%3Cspan%3EMaine%20followed%20by%20taking%20Trump%20off%20the%20ballot.%20Trump%20has%20appealed%20the%20Colarado%20ruling%20in%20the%20SC%20.%20Unlike%20the%20Colorado%20judgement%2C%20the%20SC%E2%80%99s%20decision%20will%20apply%20to%20all%20states%20and%20if%20it%20upholds%20the%20lower%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgement%2C%20Trump%20will%20effectively%20not%20be%20able%20to%20run%20for%20President.%20What%20the%20five%20men%20and%20four%20women%20of%20the%20SC%20decide%20could%20potentially%20change%20history%2C%20and%20the%20fates%20of%20millions%20of%20people%20around%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22800%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3.jpg%20800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F04%2F08132647%2Fdownload-3-300x200.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-521330%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22533%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ETrump%20supporters%20marching%20on%20the%20US%20Capitol%20on%206%20January%202021.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20try%20and%20predict%20the%20outcome%20of%20a%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20decision%20is%20a%20lot%20like%20reading%20tea%20leaves%2C%20especially%20with%20a%20court%20as%20heavily%20politicised%20as%20the%20present%20one.%20The%20current%20court%20is%20the%20most%20conservative%20in%20US%20history%2C%20with%20six%20conservative%20judges%20to%20three%20liberal%20judges.%20Three%20of%20the%20judges%20were%20appointed%20by%20Donald%20Trump%20and%20have%20been%20instrumental%20in%20driving%20an%20extremist%20conservative%20agenda%2C%20overturning%20the%20right%20to%20abortion%2C%20restricting%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20ability%20to%20make%20environmental%20regulations%2C%20and%20striking%20down%20the%20Biden%20administration%E2%80%99s%20plan%20to%20forgive%20%24400%20billion%20in%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGiven%20the%20majority%E2%80%99s%20egregious%20political%20bias%2C%20there%20is%20a%20fair%20expectation%20that%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20rule%20in%20favour%20of%20Trump%2C%20who%20looks%20certain%20to%20win%20the%20Republican%20presidential%20nomination%20by%20a%20landslide.%20Even%20discounting%20political%20bias%2C%20there%20are%20other%20reasons%20that%20would%20give%20both%20the%20conservative%20and%20liberal%20justices%20pause.%20Trump%20has%20conducted%20his%20campaign%20around%20shrill%20propaganda%20that%20the%20Democrats%20stole%20the%20previous%20election%20from%20him%20and%20all%20the%20criminal%20cases%20against%20him%20are%20political%20persecutions%20intended%20to%20keep%20him%20from%20winning%20the%20next%20election.%20A%20judgement%20that%20prevents%20Trump%20from%20running%20for%20office%20is%20sure%20to%20result%20in%20massive%20demonstrations%20from%20millions%20of%20his%20supporters%20and%20probably%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENonetheless%2C%20there%20are%20political%2C%20legal%2C%20and%20institutional%20reasons%20that%20make%20a%20ruling%20against%20Trump%20possible.%20Politically%2C%20it%20is%20not%20clear%20if%20the%20loyalty%20of%20the%20conservative%20judges%20is%20to%20the%20insurgent%20Trump%20MAGA%20faction%20of%20the%20Republican%20party%20or%20to%20the%20traditional%20Republican%20establishment.%20While%20Trump%20has%20been%20steadily%20taking%20over%20the%20Republican%20party%20based%20on%20the%20almost%20religious%20support%20of%20the%20Republican%20base%2C%20the%20Republican%20establishment%20as%20well%20as%20the%20traditional%20corporate%20interests%20that%20back%20it%2C%20have%20made%20it%20clear%20in%20private%20that%20Trump%20is%20a%20problem%20that%20they%20would%20like%20to%20be%20rid%20of%2C%20so%20as%20to%20return%20the%20Republican%20party%20to%20a%20traditional%20conservative%20party%20rather%20than%20the%20right%20wing%20extremist%20party%20Trump%20is%20fashioning%20it%20into.%20Many%20of%20the%20conservative%20judges%2C%20especially%20those%20appointed%20by%20Trump%E2%80%99s%20Republican%20predecessor%20George%20W.%20Bush%20might%20be%20sympathetic%20to%20this%20view%20and%20might%20not%20be%20averse%20to%20accomplishing%20by%20judicial%20fiat%20what%20the%20Republican%20party%20cannot%20accomplish%20politically.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20are%20institutional%20reasons%20too.%20The%20SC%20has%20been%20plagued%20by%20scandals%2C%20especially%20that%20concerning%20financial%20impropriety%20by%20Justice%20Clarence%20Thomas%2C%20whose%20wife%20also%20came%20under%20the%20scanner%20for%20links%20to%20the%20larger%20January%206%20insurrection.%20Public%20confidence%20in%20the%20SC%20is%20at%20its%20lowest%20point%20in%20decades.%20The%20chief%20justice%20John%20Robert%20is%20keen%20to%20protect%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20reputation%20and%20this%20gives%20the%20SC%20incentive%20not%20to%20be%20seen%20favouring%20Trump%20and%20to%20judge%20the%20case%20on%20its%20merits.%20As%20far%20as%20far%20as%20the%20substantive%20legal%20issues%20are%20concerned%2C%20the%20SC%20need%20only%20to%20apply%20the%20law%20to%20kick%20Trump%20off%20the%20ballot.%20The%20fourteenth%20amendment%20only%20requires%20that%20someone%20participates%20in%20an%20insurrection.%20They%20need%20not%20be%20charged%20of%20any%20crime%2C%20let%20alone%20convicted.%20Having%20delivered%20a%20televised%20address%20to%20his%20followers%20to%20march%20on%20Capitol%20Hill%2C%20it%20is%20hard%20to%20argue%20that%20Trump%20did%20not%20participate%20in%20the%20insurrection.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20lawyers%20argued%20in%20the%20Colorado%20court%20that%20even%20if%20he%20had%20participated%20in%20an%20insurrection%2C%20the%20fourteenth%20amendment%20provision%20should%20not%20be%20applied%2C%20because%20it%20would%20rob%20the%20voters%20of%20the%20right%20to%20chose%20who%20they%20want%20for%20President.%20The%20Colorado%20court%2C%20which%20had%207%20liberal%20judges%20appointed%20by%20Democrat%20presidents%2C%20was%20split%20on%20the%20decision%204-3.%20But%20ironically%2C%20the%20conservative%20judges%20on%20the%20SC%20would%20find%20it%20far%20more%20difficult%20to%20question%20the%20majority%20opinion%20disbarring%20Trump%20if%20they%20follow%20their%20own%20conservative%20legal%20philosophy.%20For%20decades%2C%20the%20judicial%20right%20has%20adopted%20a%20narrowly%20defined%20criterion%20called%20intentionalism%20which%20says%20the%20meaning%20of%20a%20law%20is%20what%20its%20framers%20intended%20it%20to%20be.%20Such%20a%20view%20of%20jurisprudence%20would%20in%20this%20case%20mean%20that%20the%20law%20disbarring%20an%20insurrectionist%20from%20public%20office%20should%20be%20applied%20in%20its%20letter%2C%20and%20other%20considerations%20which%20found%20weight%20with%20the%20dissenting%20liberal%20judges%20of%20the%20Colorado%20court%2C%20should%20have%20no%20bearing%20on%20the%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWill%20the%20US%20Supreme%20Court%20do%20its%20job%20and%20apply%20the%20law%20to%20Trump%3F%20Given%20that%20Trump%20has%20been%20recently%20accused%20of%20echoing%20Hitler%20in%20his%20attacks%20on%20immigrants%2C%20it%20is%20a%20curious%20coincidence%20that%20exactly%20100%20years%20ago%2C%20a%20court%20in%20Germany%20heard%20a%20case%20of%20insurrection%20against%20the%20government%20by%20a%20man%20named%20Adolf%20Hitler.%20The%20court%20had%20enough%20evidence%20to%20lock%20Hitler%20up%20for%20life%20and%20throw%20away%20the%20key.%20Instead%20it%20chose%20to%20sympathise%20with%20Hitler%20politically%20and%20sentenced%20him%20to%20five%20years%20in%20prison%20with%20parole%20in%20six%20months.%20Hitler%20eventually%20served%20only%20nine%20months%20and%20would%20go%20on%20to%20complete%20his%20aim%20of%20overthrowing%20German%20democracy.%20The%20three%20judges%20who%20had%20sworn%20an%20oath%20to%20uphold%20the%20law%2C%20could%20have%20prevented%20the%20greatest%20catastrophe%20in%20human%20history%20if%20they%20had%20only%20done%20their%20job.%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20would%20do%20well%20to%20look%20to%20the%20court%20of%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EGovind%20Krishnan%20V%20is%20a%20long-form%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%20He%20won%20the%202014%20Red%20Ink%20Award%20for%20Human%20Rights%20reporting.%20He%20is%20a%20published%20poet%20and%20is%20deeply%20interested%20in%20Western%20philosophy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704436213000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F08124936%2FDonald_Trump_25681459801.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fwill-the-sc-rule-in-trumps-favour-to-keep-his-presidential-ambitions-alive%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20former%20president%20has%20already%20sought%20to%20convey%20that%20if%20he%20stands%20a%20chance%20to%20contest%20again%20and%20returns%20to%20power%2C%20he%20would%20oversee%20a%20totalitarian%20fracturing%20of%20American%20democracy%2C%20with%20grave%20consequences%20for%20the%20rest%20of%20th