023.%20Central%20banks%20bought%20over%20800%20tonnes%20of%20gold%20in%202022%2C%20compared%20to%20just%20450%20tonnes%20in%202021%2C%20a%20near-100%25%20increase.%202023%20also%20saw%20well%20over%20800%20tonnes%20of%20gold%20being%20bought%20by%20central%20banks.%20The%20surge%20in%20gold%20buying%20since%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20is%20significant%20and%20it%20picked%20up%20even%20more%20after%20the%20Israeli%20assault%20on%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeopolitical%20uncertainties%20have%20caused%20a%20big%20rush%20to%20buy%20gold%2C%20even%20as%20global%20economic%20weakness%20and%20persistent%20world%20inflation%20make%20the%20yellow%20metal%20ever%20so%20attractive%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%20Experts%20suggest%20that%20gold%20will%20remain%20a%20defensive%20investment%20preference%20in%20the%20near%20future.%20Gold%20has%20given%2015%25%20return%20in%202023%20and%20its%20average%20annual%20return%20over%20the%20last%20five%20years%20has%20also%20been%20about%2015%25%20(in%20rupee%20terms).%20Perhaps%20no%20other%20asset%20class%20has%20given%20such%20returns%20globally.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20gold%20is%20being%20watched%20very%20eagerly%20by%20big%20investors%2C%20even%20as%20the%20IMF%20has%20cautioned%20that%20the%20world%20inflation%20rate%20is%20not%20going%20to%20come%20down%20to%20the%20comfort%20zone%20of%20central%20banks%20by%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGenerally%2C%20the%20attraction%20for%20gold%20increases%20when%20governments%20around%20the%20world%20become%20reckless%20borrowers%2C%20creating%20macroeconomic%20instability%20and%20the%20risk%20of%20persistent%20inflation.%20These%20conditions%20already%20existed%20before%20Covid%20but%20were%20hugely%20exacerbated%20thereafter%20as%20most%20governments%2C%20especially%20in%20the%20developed%20world%2C%20went%20on%20a%20massive%20borrowing%20spree%20to%20protect%20their%20citizens%20against%20a%20possible%20economic%20implosion.%20The%20unprecedented%20fiscal%20and%20monetary%20stimuluses%20are%20yet%20to%20be%20rolled%20back%20to%20reasonable%20levels.%20It%20is%20in%20such%20times%20that%20gold%20as%20an%20asset%20class%20is%20seen%20as%20a%20saviour.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20overall%20public%20debt%20accumulated%20by%20world%20governments%20stood%20at%20%2497%20trillion%20in%C2%A0%202023%2C%20which%20is%2040%25%20more%20than%20what%20it%20was%20in%202019.%20The%20US%20alone%20holds%2033%25%20of%20this%20cumulative%20world%20public%20debt.%20The%20US%2C%20Japan%20and%20many%20European%20economies%20have%20government%20debt%20to%20GDP%20ratios%20ranging%20from%20123%25%20to%20260%25.%20India%E2%80%99s%20debt%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20was%2081%25%20in%202022-23%20and%20the%20IMF%20recently%20warned%20it%20could%20touch%20100%25%20by%202028.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aggregate%20global%20debt%2C%20which%20includes%20borrowings%20by%20governments%2C%20households%20and%20the%20private%20sector%2C%20was%20%24307%20trillion%20in%20the%20first%20half%20of%202023.%20It%20has%20increased%20by%20%24100%20trillion%20over%20just%20the%20last%20decade.%20It%20shows%20the%20sheer%20pace%20of%20debt%20accumulation%20by%20governments%2C%20households%20and%20the%20private%20sector%20together.%20The%20aggregate%20of%20government%2C%20household%20and%20private%20sector%20debt%20stands%20at%20a%20whopping%20336%25%20of%20world%20GDP.%20The%20largest%20economies%20in%20the%20world%20today%20have%20the%20most%20serious%20debt%20problem.%20This%20is%20not%20good%20either%20for%20stable%20economic%20growth%20or%20for%20keeping%20inflation%20under%20control.%20There%20is%20also%20uncertainty%20over%20how%20long%20the%20US%20dollar%20will%20hold%20its%20own%20as%20a%20leading%20currency%2C%20if%20such%20conditions%20persist%20for%20long.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgainst%20this%20backdrop%20it%20is%20no%20surprise%20that%20gold%20is%20being%20seen%20as%20a%20very%20attractive%20investment%20option%20for%20some%20time%20to%20come.%20War%20and%20geopolitical%20instability%20lend%20further%20weight%20to%20this%20sentiment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20piece%20was%20first%20published%20on%20The%20India%20Cable%20%E2%80%93%20a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%20The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20updated%20and%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%20click%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Ftheindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704425338000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F05085816%2Fjingming-pan-iYsrkq5qq0Q-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fgold-glitters-in-an-uncertain-world%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Geopolitical%20uncertainties%20have%20caused%20a%20big%20rush%20to%20buy%20gold%2C%20even%20as%20global%20economic%20weakness%20and%20persistent%20world%20inflation%20make%20the%20yellow%20metal%20ever%20so%20attractive%20in%20the%20medium%20term.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fgold-glitters-in-an-uncertain-world%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Blinken%20heads%20to%20Middle%20East%20in%20firefight%20mode%20as%20risk%20of%20escalation%20grows%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1704422340000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-antony-blinken-us-secretary-of-state_6412498.jpg%3F20240105030230%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fantony-blinken-heads-to-middle-east-in-firefight-mode-as-risk-of-escalation-grows-13042407%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22'The%20risk%20is%20real%20and%20concern%20is%20high.'%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fantony-blinken-heads-to-middle-east-in-firefight-mode-as-risk-of-escalation-grows-13042407%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-co